WEBVTT

00:04.833 --> 00:05.833 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Good evening.

00:05.833 --> 00:07.500 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
I'm Judy Woodruff.

00:07.500 --> 00:10.466 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
On the "NewsHour"
tonight: a turn in the
Russia investigation.

00:10.466 --> 00:15.466 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Special counsel Robert Mueller
moves beyond the 2016 election,
investigating possible

00:17.433 --> 00:21.166 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
obstruction of justice
by the president since he
took office in January.

00:23.633 --> 00:26.766 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Also ahead: Twelve Turkish
security agents are
charged after a violent
clash with protesters

00:28.833 --> 00:33.100 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
outside Turkey's embassy in
D.C., testing already shaky
diplomatic relations between

00:33.933 --> 00:36.500 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
the two countries.

00:36.500 --> 00:40.033 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Then: a look at companies,
including one owned by
Jared Kushner's family,
that take advantage

00:42.133 --> 00:46.633 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
of tax breaks to create jobs in
high unemployment areas, but do
those jobs end up going to those

00:48.133 --> 00:49.400 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
who need them?

00:49.400 --> 00:51.733 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
MAN: Several of us tried
to get a job downtown.

00:51.733 --> 00:53.733 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
But they're not hiring us.

00:53.733 --> 00:57.733 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
I don't know no one at all
who has no type of job from
downtown at Trump Towers or who

00:58.900 --> 01:00.466 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
informed anyone
else about the jobs.

01:00.466 --> 01:05.233 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: All that and more
on tonight's "PBS NewsHour."

01:08.033 --> 01:10.900 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
(BREAK)

01:10.900 --> 01:15.900 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: President Trump
is now under scrutiny for
possible obstruction of justice,

01:20.733 --> 01:22.800 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
and he's fighting back.

01:22.800 --> 01:27.366 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
This follows news reports that
special counsel Bob Mueller has
broadened his probe originally

01:28.700 --> 01:30.766 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
focused on Russia
meddling in the election.

01:30.766 --> 01:35.266 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
On Twitter today, the president
complained - - quote -- "They
made up a phony collusion

01:35.266 --> 01:40.266 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
with the Russians story, found
zero proof, so now they go
for obstruction of justice.

01:40.800 --> 01:42.933 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
Nice."

01:42.933 --> 01:46.800 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Later, Mr. Trump charged that
Hillary Clinton committed a list
of infractions, and was cleared

01:47.300 --> 01:49.433 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
anyway.

01:49.433 --> 01:53.066 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
There's also word that Vice
President Mike Pence has hired
outside legal counsel to deal

01:53.966 --> 01:56.000 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
with the Russia investigations.

01:56.000 --> 02:00.600 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
His office tells The Washington
Post that former U.S. attorney
Richard Cullen will handle

02:00.600 --> 02:04.600 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
inquiries from
congressional committees
and the special counsel.

02:04.600 --> 02:07.366 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
The president hired his own
private lawyer last month.

02:07.366 --> 02:11.733 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
We will examine all of this, and
talk to the vice chairman of the
Senate Intelligence Committee,

02:11.733 --> 02:15.100 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Senator Mark Warner, right
after the news summary.

02:15.100 --> 02:20.100 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
The U.S. Senate today
overwhelmingly approved
new sanctions against
both Iran and Russia.

02:21.566 --> 02:24.466 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
The overall bill is aimed
at Iran's missile program.

02:24.466 --> 02:29.466 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
An amendment expands sanctions
on Russia for meddling
in last year's election.

02:31.466 --> 02:33.966 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Senate Minority Leader Chuck
Schumer said today it sends a
message to Russian President

02:33.966 --> 02:36.366 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
Vladimir Putin and
to President Trump.

02:36.366 --> 02:38.466 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
SEN.

02:38.466 --> 02:39.933 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
CHUCK SCHUMER (D-NY), Minority
Leader: Not only did we pass
a new round of tough sanctions

02:39.933 --> 02:42.300 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
for Russia's meddling
in our election.

02:42.300 --> 02:47.300 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
We codified existing
sanctions into law, making
them harder to lift.

02:49.300 --> 02:52.300 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Any idea of the president's
that he can lift sanctions on
his own for whatever reason are

02:52.300 --> 02:54.900 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
dashed by this legislation.

02:54.900 --> 02:59.866 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Putin fired
back during a national
call-in show in Moscow,
and said the sanctions

03:01.166 --> 03:03.666 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
say more about the
U.S. than about Russia.

03:03.666 --> 03:07.233 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
VLADIMIR PUTIN, Russian
President (through translator):
Why have they started to talk

03:07.233 --> 03:10.000 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
about introducing these
sanctions with no grounds?

03:10.000 --> 03:14.866 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Of course it is evidence of
continuing internal political
struggle in the United States.

03:14.866 --> 03:18.633 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
If there weren't other problems,
they would have thought up
something else to hold Russia

03:18.633 --> 03:22.433 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
back, as it has always been, a
policy of holding Russia back.

03:22.433 --> 03:26.233 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: We will take
a closer look at the Senate's
sanctions bill a little later

03:26.233 --> 03:28.800 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
in the program.

03:28.800 --> 03:32.333 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
A leading Republican in the
House of Representatives,
Majority Whip Steve
Scalise, remains in critical

03:34.166 --> 03:38.266 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
condition tonight after a
gunman shot him during a
congressional baseball practice.

03:38.266 --> 03:42.933 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
A lobbyist who was wounded is
also in critical condition.

03:42.933 --> 03:46.733 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
President Trump visited
Scalise in a Washington
hospital last night.

03:46.733 --> 03:51.733 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Today, at the White House, he
said Scalise's recovery will
be more difficult than people

03:52.200 --> 03:53.900 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
thought.

03:53.900 --> 03:56.900 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
DONALD TRUMP, President
of the United States:
He's in some trouble.

03:56.900 --> 03:59.000 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
He's a great fighter and
he's going to be OK, we hope.

03:59.000 --> 04:03.166 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And Steve in his own way may
have brought some unity to
our long divided country.

04:05.366 --> 04:10.366 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And I have a feeling that Steve
has made a great sacrifice,
but there could be some unity

04:12.366 --> 04:14.100 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
being brought to our country.

04:14.100 --> 04:16.100 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
Let's hope so.

04:16.100 --> 04:20.366 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: The gunman, James
Hodgkinson of Illinois, died
after being shot by police.

04:22.466 --> 04:26.166 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
Meanwhile, the annual
congressional baseball
game is being played
tonight, raising money

04:26.166 --> 04:28.233 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
for charity.

04:28.233 --> 04:32.566 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
The American college student
released from North Korea, and
now in a coma, has a massive

04:33.300 --> 04:35.833 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
loss of brain tissue.

04:35.833 --> 04:39.833 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Doctors at the University
of Cincinnati Medical
Center said today that
Otto Warmbier suffered

04:40.700 --> 04:42.766 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
a severe neurological injury.

04:42.766 --> 04:45.633 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
They could not say
if he was beaten.

04:45.633 --> 04:49.933 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Warmbier's father condemned
the North Koreans, but said
the family wants to move on.

04:49.933 --> 04:53.300 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
FRED WARMBIER, Father of Otto
Warmbier: What I would say
to the North Korean regime, I

04:53.300 --> 04:58.300 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
would say I'm so proud of
Otto, my son, who has been in
a pariah regime for the last 18

05:03.566 --> 05:06.066 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
months, brutalized
and terrorized.

05:06.066 --> 05:08.966 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
And he's now home
with his family.

05:08.966 --> 05:11.966 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
And I'm just tremendously
proud of Otto.

05:11.966 --> 05:13.966 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
His spirit is with us.

05:13.966 --> 05:18.633 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: The State
Department now says that a U.S.
diplomat who went to North Korea

05:18.633 --> 05:23.633 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
to secure Warmbier's release
also contacted three other
Americans being held.

05:25.033 --> 05:27.133 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
The department wouldn't
comment on their conditions.

05:27.133 --> 05:31.666 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
In London, rescue crews have
pulled more bodies from a
burned-out apartment tower.

05:33.600 --> 05:37.233 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
The death toll in Wednesday's
fire reached at least 17
today, amid rising outrage.

05:38.600 --> 05:41.233 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Paul Davies of Independent
Television News has this report.

05:41.233 --> 05:45.733 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
PAUL DAVIES: A second dawn
brought no end to the agony.

05:45.733 --> 05:50.733 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
There are no flames now, but
this smoldering shell that was
once home to so many families

05:51.900 --> 05:55.900 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
still holds an unknown
number of their bodies.

05:55.900 --> 06:00.900 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Fire crews believe, in flats
not yet safe to enter, there are
a whole families who couldn't

06:02.066 --> 06:04.766 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
get out or obeyed the
instruction to stay put.

06:04.766 --> 06:07.200 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
Many, many remain missing.

06:07.200 --> 06:09.700 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
And it could take weeks
to confirm their fate.

06:09.700 --> 06:12.233 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
DANY COTTON, London Fire
Brigade: It's the upper floors
that will be more challenging

06:12.233 --> 06:16.100 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
and will need some
additional shoring for us
to be able to get in there.

06:16.100 --> 06:18.166 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
The size of this building,
it could take weeks.

06:18.166 --> 06:19.600 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
I want to be realistic.

06:19.600 --> 06:21.566 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
This is a very long process.

06:21.566 --> 06:25.933 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
PAUL DAVIES: These images
show the destruction on the
ground floor of Grenfell Tower.

06:29.633 --> 06:34.633 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
This is the area least affected
by that all-consuming fire.

06:36.066 --> 06:39.933 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
As this photograph shows,
it gets worse as you go up.

06:39.933 --> 06:42.900 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
Very few escaped
the higher floors.

06:42.900 --> 06:47.233 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
If the initial response to
this tragedy was horror, as the
hours have passed, there have

06:47.233 --> 06:49.700 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
been mounting questions
and mounting anger.

06:49.700 --> 06:50.700 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
WOMAN: There is a
system in place.

06:50.700 --> 06:51.700 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
That is the product.

06:51.700 --> 06:52.833 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
That is it.

06:52.833 --> 06:55.166 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
WOMAN: There's nothing at all.

06:55.166 --> 06:57.266 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
Yes, but they're lying.

06:57.266 --> 07:02.033 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
PAUL DAVIES: Labor's
leader visiting the area
heard the concerns of
residents who say fears

07:03.466 --> 07:05.966 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
they'd expressed about the
tower's safety were ignored.

07:05.966 --> 07:07.833 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
MAN: Someone has to
be held accountable.

07:07.833 --> 07:09.800 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
Someone has to be
held responsible.

07:09.800 --> 07:11.866 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
We don't want it kicked
to the long grass.

07:11.866 --> 07:15.833 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
We don't want the government to
sort of hide with some hollow
platitude about lessons being

07:15.833 --> 07:17.866 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
learned.

07:17.866 --> 07:20.700 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
PAUL DAVIES: The prime minister
paid her own private visit to
Grenfell Tower this morning

07:20.700 --> 07:25.533 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
and was criticized for meeting
only the emergency teams,
and not the local community.

07:25.533 --> 07:28.200 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
AFAF BADR, London:
People are very angry.

07:28.200 --> 07:29.333 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
People are crying.

07:29.333 --> 07:31.133 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
People are lost, missing.

07:31.133 --> 07:33.266 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
She's the prime minister.

07:33.266 --> 07:35.300 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
Where is she?

07:35.300 --> 07:38.966 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
PAUL DAVIES: London's mayor
visiting the scene said
anger was understandable.

07:38.966 --> 07:43.933 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
SADIQ KHAN, Mayor of
London: We can see the
anger in the community,
justifiably so, because

07:43.933 --> 07:45.533 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
many members of the
community have been saying...

07:45.533 --> 07:46.533 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
WOMAN: Not just the community.

07:46.533 --> 07:48.133 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
It's everyone outside as well.

07:48.133 --> 07:50.633 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
MAN: Fed up with
these politicians.

07:50.633 --> 07:51.633 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
No handshakes.

07:51.633 --> 07:53.666 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
We want action, not handshakes.

07:53.666 --> 07:58.600 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
PAUL DAVIES: Sadiq Khan said
the inquiry should be immediate
and that no one should have to

07:59.800 --> 08:02.433 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
wait two years to find
out why this happened.

08:02.433 --> 08:07.433 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Both Britain's
national government and
local police have now
opened investigations

08:08.066 --> 08:10.100 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
into the fire.

08:10.100 --> 08:14.666 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Islamist fighters in Somalia
attacked a popular restaurant
overnight and killed at least 31

08:15.133 --> 08:17.100 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
people.

08:17.100 --> 08:19.833 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
It happened in the country's
capital, Mogadishu, and
involved five gunmen.

08:19.833 --> 08:24.833 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
The Al-Shabaab militants
detonated a car bomb, and then
stormed inside, taking hostages.

08:26.200 --> 08:30.200 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Witnesses said they shot
victims at point-blank range.

08:30.200 --> 08:34.166 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Somali security forces
finally killed the gunmen
early this morning.

08:34.166 --> 08:39.166 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Back in this country, jurors in
the Bill Cosby sexual assault
trial deliberated into the

08:40.533 --> 08:43.300 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
evening again, after reporting
that they're deadlocked.

08:43.300 --> 08:46.700 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
The judge in Norristown,
Pennsylvania, told
them to keep at it.

08:46.700 --> 08:51.700 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
The 79-year-old Cosby is
accused of drugging and
molesting a woman in 2004.

08:53.666 --> 08:58.066 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And on Wall Street, the Dow
Jones industrial average lost
14 points to close below 21360.

08:58.066 --> 09:03.066 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
The Nasdaq fell 29, and
the S&amp;P 500 slipped five.

