20:24.733 --> 20:28.300 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
address any issues arising out
of the Russia investigation.

20:28.300 --> 20:29.366 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
Do you have a comment on that?

20:29.366 --> 20:31.466 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
SEN.

20:31.466 --> 20:34.666 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
MARK WARNER: No, I don't have
a comment, but I just -- other
than the fact that it would

20:34.666 --> 20:39.666 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
be helpful if the administration
actually collaborated and
cooperated with all of us.

20:41.700 --> 20:45.933 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
What the Russians did in 2016
in the United States, the
Russians have also done in the

20:47.433 --> 20:49.533 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
French elections, they will
do in the German elections.

20:49.533 --> 20:53.900 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
And, as a state that
has statewide elections
this year, I'm concerned
about their ongoing

20:55.400 --> 20:58.800 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
efforts to try to, frankly, sow
chaos in our democratic process.

20:58.800 --> 21:00.166 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
And let me be clear.

21:00.166 --> 21:01.233 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
This is not about
relitigating 2016.

21:01.233 --> 21:02.233 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Right.

21:02.233 --> 21:04.233 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
SEN.

21:04.233 --> 21:05.500 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
MARK WARNER: It's not about
the Russians being for
Republicans or Democrats.

21:05.500 --> 21:06.933 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
The Russians are for
their own interests.

21:06.933 --> 21:09.533 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
And we have to be careful about
this new form of conflict.

21:09.533 --> 21:13.566 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: But just
very quickly, Senator,
so I understand, you're
saying the administration

21:13.566 --> 21:15.133 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
is not collaborating
right now with you?

21:15.133 --> 21:16.633 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
SEN.

21:16.633 --> 21:18.666 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
MARK WARNER: I wish there
was closer cooperation.

21:18.666 --> 21:21.800 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
There are a number of members
of the administration who
volunteered to come forward.

21:21.800 --> 21:24.933 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
There are a number of
individuals that work
on the Trump campaign.

21:24.933 --> 21:29.933 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
But I don't see what
value is added by the
president's constant
dismissal of the seriousness

21:32.666 --> 21:34.733 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
of this threat.

21:34.733 --> 21:37.666 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Senator Mark
Warner, the vice chairman of
the Senate Select Committee on

21:37.666 --> 21:39.633 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
Intelligence, we thank you.

21:39.633 --> 21:40.733 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
SEN.

21:40.733 --> 21:45.733 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
MARK WARNER: Thank you, Judy.

21:48.233 --> 21:51.133 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: As we
reported earlier in the
program, the Senate today
overwhelmingly passed

21:53.633 --> 21:55.766 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
new sanctions against Iran.

21:55.766 --> 21:58.466 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
But a key amendment makes
that bill even broader.

21:58.466 --> 22:00.833 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
It now includes sanctions
aimed at Russia.

22:00.833 --> 22:05.566 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
This is five months after U.S.
intelligence agencies made
public that Russian President

22:05.566 --> 22:10.300 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
Vladimir Putin ordered
cyber-interference
in the 2016 election.

22:10.300 --> 22:13.800 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
Lisa Desjardins has
been following the vote,
and she joins me now.

22:13.800 --> 22:15.833 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
So, Lisa, tell us what
these Russia sanctions are.

22:15.833 --> 22:17.666 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
LISA DESJARDINS: These are
not just symbolic, Judy.

22:17.666 --> 22:18.966 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
These are significant sanctions.

22:18.966 --> 22:20.866 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
Let's take a quick look.

22:20.866 --> 22:24.066 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
First of all, they target
Russian industries,
especially the energy sector.

22:24.066 --> 22:28.633 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Those sanctions would include
things limiting U.S. companies,
prohibiting them from working

22:28.633 --> 22:30.766 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
with Russian firms, say,
exploring the Arctic.

22:30.766 --> 22:32.866 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
That's a big deal.

22:32.866 --> 22:36.866 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
Also, this would target
individuals working in
defense or intelligence,
individual Russians.

22:36.866 --> 22:38.800 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
There are some new
powers in here.

22:38.800 --> 22:42.166 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
The Treasury would get
access to U.S. bank records
of Russian oligarchs.

22:42.166 --> 22:47.166 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Also, $250 million for
a countering Russia
influence fund that would
focus on cyber-security,

22:48.333 --> 22:50.333 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
but also could be
some U.S. propaganda.

22:50.333 --> 22:55.033 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: And, separately,
the Senate passed an amendment
to this that affects the

22:55.666 --> 22:56.500 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
president.

22:56.500 --> 22:57.766 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
Tell us about that.

22:57.766 --> 22:59.733 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
LISA DESJARDINS: This
is remarkable, Judy.

22:59.733 --> 23:03.333 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
This is a Republican Congress
asserting power with a
Republican president in office.

23:04.500 --> 23:06.400 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
Let's look at exactly
how that would work.

23:06.400 --> 23:09.200 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
If this president wanted
to roll back any of these
sanctions, he would have to give

23:09.200 --> 23:12.866 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
Congress 30-day notice
under this amendment.

23:12.866 --> 23:17.366 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Congress could then
disapprove and ultimately
block the president from
rolling back sanctions

23:17.366 --> 23:19.366 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
with a two-thirds vote.

23:19.366 --> 23:22.733 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Essentially, Judy, what the
Senate is saying here is, we
think Congress should set Russia

23:22.733 --> 23:24.766 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
policy now, not the president.

23:24.766 --> 23:27.266 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
JUDY WOODRUFF: And
what is the White House
saying about all this?

23:27.266 --> 23:30.033 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
LISA DESJARDINS: The White
House today said it's
reviewing these sanctions.

23:30.033 --> 23:34.100 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
No secret the president is in
a very tricky position here,
not just because of this Russia

23:34.100 --> 23:38.400 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
investigation, but because he
and his secretary of state have
said they don't think this is

23:38.400 --> 23:40.666 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
a good time to increase
sanctions on Russia.

23:40.666 --> 23:42.700 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
They think it could backfire.

23:42.700 --> 23:47.333 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
But it's interesting, Judy, the
Senate attached these Russia
sanctions to an Iran sanctions

23:47.333 --> 23:50.133 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
bill that the president
wants to sign.

23:50.133 --> 23:54.266 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Meanwhile, Democrats are worried
about the Iran sanctions,
worried that that could cause

23:54.266 --> 23:59.133 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
problems with the Iran deal,
which leaves the president
deciding, does he swallow these

23:59.133 --> 24:03.500 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Russia sanctions that go with
an Iran deal he likes at a time
of the Russia investigation?

24:03.500 --> 24:05.533 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
We have to wait and see.

24:05.533 --> 24:07.833 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: And in two
seconds, if the president were
to veto this, the assumption

24:07.833 --> 24:08.866 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
is, it would be overridden?

24:08.866 --> 24:10.266 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
LISA DESJARDINS: That's correct.

24:10.266 --> 24:11.933 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
It passed with 98
votes in the Senate.

24:11.933 --> 24:13.600 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
Absolutely, they would
override that veto.

24:13.600 --> 24:16.900 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Lisa
Desjardins, thank you.

24:16.900 --> 24:21.900 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
LISA DESJARDINS: My pleasure.

24:24.333 --> 24:28.233 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: A new
flash point in the tense
and fraying alliance
between the United States

24:30.633 --> 24:35.466 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
and Turkey, after Turkish
security forces attacked
protesters during
President Erdogan's

24:36.333 --> 24:38.800 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
recent visit to Washington, D.C.

24:38.800 --> 24:40.466 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
Hari Sreenivasan has our report.

24:40.466 --> 24:44.733 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
And a warning: Images in this
report may disturb some viewers.

24:44.733 --> 24:49.733 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
HARI SREENIVASAN: It's been
one month since attackers
launched into protesters outside

24:50.933 --> 24:53.566 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
the Turkish ambassador's
residence in Washington.

24:53.566 --> 24:58.433 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Now D.C. officials have issued
warrants on assault charges.

24:58.433 --> 25:00.866 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
Police Chief Peter Newsham:

25:00.866 --> 25:03.200 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
PETER NEWSHAM, Acting
Washington, D.C., Police
Chief: We all saw the
violence that was perpetrated

25:03.200 --> 25:06.200 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
against peaceful demonstrators
here in Washington,
D.C., and it's just
something we're not going

25:06.200 --> 25:08.733 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
to tolerate.

25:08.733 --> 25:10.833 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
HARI SREENIVASAN: The
demonstrators had gathered
at a park shortly after
Turkey's president,

25:10.833 --> 25:13.900 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
Recep Tayyip Erdogan,
met with President Trump
at the White House.

25:13.900 --> 25:18.900 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Then, as Erdogan arrived
at the ambassador's
residence, trouble started.

25:20.766 --> 25:23.066 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Video showed security
guards and supporters teeing
off on the protesters.

25:23.066 --> 25:28.066 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
D.C. police officers tried to
separate and calm the crowd,
but nine people were hurt.

25:30.100 --> 25:33.366 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
Two people were arrested
that day, and two more
were apprehended by
U.S. Marshals yesterday.

25:34.833 --> 25:37.166 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Now there are 12 new warrants
for Turkish security officers.

25:37.166 --> 25:40.233 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Most, if not all, returned
home after the attack.

25:40.233 --> 25:42.566 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
Two Canadians are
also being sought.

25:42.566 --> 25:45.133 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
It's unclear why they
allegedly joined the melee.

25:45.133 --> 25:48.800 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Chief Newsham is calling for
the suspects to surrender
and not fight extradition.

25:48.800 --> 25:53.800 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
PETER NEWSHAM: If you
are a law-abiding person,
and you feel like you
didn't do anything wrong,

25:57.733 --> 26:01.133 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
then please present yourself
here to answer to these charges.

26:01.133 --> 26:04.900 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
HARI SREENIVASAN:
Erdogan responded to the
charges, and said the
demonstrators were associated

26:04.900 --> 26:09.900 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
with Kurdish militants
who've been engaged in a
long insurgency against
the Turkish government.

26:11.933 --> 26:14.033 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
RECEP TAYYIP ERDOGAN, Turkish
President (through translator):
Of course we're going the fight

26:14.033 --> 26:16.300 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
this on legal and
political grounds.

26:16.300 --> 26:18.366 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
What kind of law is this?

26:18.366 --> 26:21.666 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
If my security guards are not
going to protect me, why would
I bring them with me to America?

26:21.666 --> 26:25.866 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
HARI SREENIVASAN: Meanwhile,
Erdogan's role in all of
this remains a question.

26:25.866 --> 26:30.866 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
After the incident, The
New York Times examined
the video and spotted
Erdogan's head of security

26:32.800 --> 26:35.933 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
