car, and then speaking into
his earpiece, just before three

26:35.933 --> 26:38.500 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
guards ran toward
the protesters.

26:38.500 --> 26:42.300 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
At the time, the State
Department said it
communicated -- quote
-- "concerns" to Turkey

26:42.300 --> 26:46.666 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
over the confrontation, and
today said -- quote - - "We
will weigh additional actions."

26:46.666 --> 26:51.666 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
STEVEN COOK, Council on Foreign
Relations: President Erdogan's
security team irresponsible,

26:52.533 --> 26:54.600 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
unprofessional and violent.

26:54.600 --> 26:56.266 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
HARI SREENIVASAN: Steven Cook
is a senior fellow with the
Council on Foreign Relations

26:56.266 --> 26:58.366 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
in Washington.

26:58.366 --> 27:01.500 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
He says relations between
Washington and Ankara are as
bad as they have ever been.

27:01.500 --> 27:06.500 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
STEVEN COOK: Charging President
Erdogan's security team
with crimes is going to add

27:08.266 --> 27:12.000 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
another element of tension
between the two countries.

27:12.000 --> 27:17.000 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
This tension will no doubt be
used by the Turkish leadership
to advance their own political

27:17.000 --> 27:21.100 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
agenda, which is only
going to cause raw feelings
here in Washington.

27:21.100 --> 27:25.200 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
HARI SREENIVASAN: The U.S.
and Turkey are already at odds
over Kurdish forces fighting

27:25.200 --> 27:27.233 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
in Syria.

27:27.233 --> 27:31.166 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And the Turks have demanded the
U.S. extradite exiled cleric
Fethullah Gulen for allegedly

27:31.166 --> 27:33.666 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
organizing last
summer's failed coup.

27:33.666 --> 27:38.500 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
For the "PBS NewsHour,"
I'm Hari Sreenivasan.

27:38.500 --> 27:43.500 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
